{"parse":{"title":"Odotheus","pageid":10604818,"revid":848274570,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Odotheus</b> (in <a href=\"/wiki/Zosimus\" title=\"Zosimus\">Zosimus</a> <i>Aedotheus</i>) was a <a href=\"/wiki/Greuthungi\" title=\"Greuthungi\">Greuthungi</a> king who in 386 led an incursion into the <a href=\"/wiki/Roman_Empire\" title=\"Roman Empire\">Roman Empire</a>. He was defeated and killed by the Roman general <a href=\"/wiki/Promotus\" title=\"Promotus\">Promotus</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> His surviving people settled in <a href=\"/wiki/Phrygia\" title=\"Phrygia\">Phrygia</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Invasion_of_Roman_Empire\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Invasion of Roman Empire</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Fate_of_Odotheus&#39;_People\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Fate of Odotheus' People</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Sources\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Sources</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Invasion_of_Roman_Empire\">Invasion of Roman Empire</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Odotheus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Invasion of Roman Empire\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>After the major Gothic entry into the Roman Empire in 376, there still remained substantial numbers of Goths in several kingdoms north and east of the lower <a href=\"/wiki/Danube\" title=\"Danube\">Danube</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> In the year 386 the king Odotheus led his people into the Empire, possibly fleeing Hunnic hegemony, but Heather (1996:103) disputes this.\nOdotheus was brought to battle and killed by the general Promotus.\nZosimus gives two versions  (4.35 and 4.38-9), generally thought to be of the same story; the second version calls them <i>Grothingi</i> and speaks of a betrayal (or entrapment) by Promotus.\nThe survivors of his people were settled in <a href=\"/wiki/Phrygia\" title=\"Phrygia\">Phrygia</a>; some were drafted into the <a href=\"/wiki/Roman_Army\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Roman Army\">Army</a> and some became agricultural labourers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"Fate_of_Odotheus.27_People\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Fate_of_Odotheus'_People\">Fate of Odotheus' People</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Odotheus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Fate of Odotheus&#039; People\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 399, <a href=\"/wiki/Tribigild\" title=\"Tribigild\">Tribigild</a>, a Gothic commander in Roman service who led a unit of these Phrygian survivors of Odotheus' kingdom,<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> rose in revolt. <a href=\"/wiki/Michael_Kulikowski\" title=\"Michael Kulikowski\">Michael Kulikowski</a> suggests the Goths of Tribigild were in fact survivors of the massacres in Asia Minor of 378/9, after the <a href=\"/wiki/Battle_of_Adrianople\" title=\"Battle of Adrianople\">Battle of Adrianople</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/wiki/Gainas\" title=\"Gainas\">Gainas</a>, another Gothic general sent to suppress him, suborned Tribigild's revolt for his own purposes. After some initial successes, Gainas was suppressed and fled north of the Danube, only to be killed by the Hunnic chieftain <a href=\"/wiki/Uldin\" title=\"Uldin\">Uldin</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> Thus perished many of Odotheus' remaining people; the fate of the rest in Phrygia is unknown.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Odotheus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Zosimus, V.36 seems to put this <i>before</i> the death of Gratian in 383, but in IV.39 he tells of Theodosius recruiting the survivors for the coming campaign against Magnus Maximus, and Claudian <i>Cos. Hon IV</i> 633\u201337 dates the victory over Odotheus by Honorius\u2019 first consulship, i.e. 386</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Heather (1996), 56</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Heather (1996), n. 10 to p. 138. \"Zosimus 4.35, 38-9, Cons. Const. s.a. 386 (= <i>CM </i>1, 244). <i>captivi</i>: Claudian <i>In Eut.</i> 2.582. <i>coloni</i>: <i>ibid</i>. 205\".</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Heather (1996), 144</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFKulikowski2006\">Kulikowski 2006</a>, p.&#160;154</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Zosimus V.21-22</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Sources\">Sources</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Odotheus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Sources\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\"><a href=\"/wiki/Peter_Heather\" title=\"Peter Heather\">Heather, Peter</a> (1996). <i>The Goths</i>. Oxford: Blackwell Publishers. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-631-16536-3\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-631-16536-3\">0-631-16536-3</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Goths&amp;rft.place=Oxford&amp;rft.pub=Blackwell+Publishers&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft.isbn=0-631-16536-3&amp;rft.aulast=Heather&amp;rft.aufirst=Peter&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AOdotheus\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite id=\"CITEREFKulokowski2006\" class=\"citation book\"><a href=\"/wiki/Michael_Kulikowski\" title=\"Michael Kulikowski\">Kulokowski, Michael</a> (October 30, 2006). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=QXM9SH4EALgC\"><i>Rome's Gothic Wars: From the Third Century to Alaric</i></a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Cambridge_University_Press\" title=\"Cambridge University Press\">Cambridge University Press</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1139458094\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1139458094\">1139458094</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">January 17,</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Rome%27s+Gothic+Wars%3A+From+the+Third+Century+to+Alaric&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2006-10-30&amp;rft.isbn=1139458094&amp;rft.aulast=Kulokowski&amp;rft.aufirst=Michael&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DQXM9SH4EALgC&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AOdotheus\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Zosimus\" title=\"Zosimus\">Zosimus</a>, <i>Novae Historiae</i> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.tertullian.org/fathers/zosimus04_book4.htm\">bk 4</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.tertullian.org/fathers/zosimus05_book5.htm\">bk 5</a></li></ul>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Europe_green_light.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Europe green light.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Europe_green_light.svg/32px-Europe_green_light.svg.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"28\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Europe_green_light.svg/48px-Europe_green_light.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Europe_green_light.svg/64px-Europe_green_light.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"260\" data-file-height=\"226\" /></a><img alt=\"Hou